1. *Sneg* je prekrio celu ulicu. (Snow covered the entire street.)
2. Ne volim *sneg* zato što mi smeta pri vožnji. (I don't like snow because it bothers me when driving.)
3. Kada padne *sneg*, deca se raduju. (When snow falls, children are happy.)
4. *Sneg* je danas bio visok skoro do kolena. (The snow was almost knee-deep today.)
5. Moramo očistiti put od *snega* da bi mogli proći autom. (We have to clear the road from the snow to be able to pass by car.)
6. Moja omiljena aktivnost zimi je pravljenje figura od *snega*. (My favorite winter activity is making snow figures.)
7. Zima je najlepša kada je sve okovano belim *snegom*. (Winter is the most beautiful when everything is covered with white snow.)
8. *Sneg* se topi kada sunce obasja. (Snow melts when the sun shines.)
9. Vozimo se kroz prelepe predele pokrivene *snegom*. (We are driving through beautiful landscapes covered in snow.)
10. U ovo doba godine možemo očekivati da će padati *sneg*. (We can expect snowfall at this time of the year.)

Note: In Serbian language, nouns and adjectives can be declined and their forms can change depending on their function in a sentence, so the word "sneg" can have different forms. However, in these examples, I highlighted the base form of the word with a star.